Citations
Date:  0/0/1971
Source:  Ten Thousand Dogs
Author:  NEWTON
Vol / Page:  168
Edition:
Quote:  Feathering: after heading sheep some dogs will wait - or feather - before attempting to 'lift' or 'pull' them. This has a quietening effect on sheep.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Loughnan Glossary
Author:  LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page:  30
Edition:
Quote:  feather: a dog feathers his sheep when handling them very, very gently. This moment occurs after he has come 'on' his sheep and has paused to gain their confidence before lifting them.
